WEBVTT

00:02.369 --> 00:03.370
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"DEVIOUS MAIDS"...</i>

00:03.370 --> 00:05.005
YOUR FATHER LOVES CHILDREN.

00:05.005 --> 00:07.508
WELL, THAT'S A CANDY-COATED LIE
IF I EVER HEARD ONE.

00:07.508 --> 00:09.109
I FELL IN LOVE
WITH A BOY.

00:09.109 --> 00:10.244
GOT PREGNANT.

00:10.244 --> 00:11.645
DADDY WAS SO ANGRY.

00:11.645 --> 00:14.481
HE WOULDN'T LET ME
KEEP THE BABY.

00:14.481 --> 00:17.251
WERE YOU SEEING HER
BEFORE YOU MOVED OUT?

00:17.251 --> 00:20.153
WE WERE JUST GOOD FRIENDS...
MOSTLY.

00:20.153 --> 00:21.655
YOU HAVE TO SHOW EVERYONE

00:21.655 --> 00:23.657
THAT YOU DON'T NEED PABLO
TO BE HAPPY.

00:23.657 --> 00:25.125
I'M CRAZY ABOUT YOU.

00:25.125 --> 00:27.160
THAT'S WHAT I EXPECT
FROM MY <i>BOYFRIEND.</i>

00:27.160 --> 00:28.495
I'M SEEING SOMEONE.

00:28.495 --> 00:30.531
YOU'RE DATING
MY POOL BOY?

00:30.531 --> 00:32.699
JUST SO YOU KNOW,
I STILL LOVE YOU.

00:32.699 --> 00:34.234
I KNOW
WE'RE MEANT TO BE TOGETHER.

00:34.234 --> 00:35.969
THEN I WILL GET HER BACK
FOR YOU.

00:35.969 --> 00:38.639
<i>IN A SAD TWIST,</i>
<i>ONE YOUNG FAN ATTEMPTED SUICIDE</i>

00:38.639 --> 00:40.641
<i>OUTSIDE</i>
<i>RUBIO'S BEVERLY HILLS HOME.</i>

00:40.641 --> 00:42.376
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
A KID STAYING HERE?

00:42.376 --> 00:44.545
MY NEPHEW IS NOT A CHILD.
HE'S 17.

00:44.545 --> 00:45.579
UH...

00:45.579 --> 00:47.047
WHERE SHOULD I PUT
MY BAGS?

00:47.047 --> 00:48.415
HAVE YOU HEARD OF
ALEJANDRO RUBIO?

00:48.415 --> 00:50.117
DID YOU HEAR
HOW HE WAS MURDERED?

00:50.117 --> 00:52.419
I AM SO SORRY FOR EVERYTHING
THAT YOU'VE GONE THROUGH.

00:52.419 --> 00:55.389
IT'S OKAY, HONEY.
IT WASN'T YOUR FAULT.

00:55.389 --> 00:57.524
CARTER KILLED ALEJANDRO.

00:57.524 --> 01:00.127
THAT MIGHT NOT BE
HOW THE REST OF US REMEMBER IT.

01:00.127 --> 01:01.528
YOU HAD NO RIGHT!

01:01.528 --> 01:02.996
OH, FOR GOD'S SAKE...

01:02.996 --> 01:04.998
THIS IS NOT YOUR HOUSE!

01:04.998 --> 01:06.500
I WANT A BRUNETTE,
YOU KNOW?

01:06.500 --> 01:08.435
SOMEONE SPICY AND ETHNIC,
LIKE YOU.

01:08.435 --> 01:09.670
DO YOU WANT
TO BE ALONE WITH HIM?

01:09.670 --> 01:11.305
A MIDDLE-AGED MAN
HAS A WORK CRUSH.

01:11.305 --> 01:12.639
I CANNOT
GO THROUGH THIS AGAIN.

01:12.639 --> 01:14.341
OKAY? THE UNCERTAINTY,
THE PARANOIA --

01:14.341 --> 01:16.243
WHAT DO YOU MEAN "AGAIN"?

01:16.243 --> 01:18.078
DAHLIA HAD AN AFFAIR.

01:24.251 --> 01:26.386
[ SIGHS ]

01:38.565 --> 01:40.601
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

01:44.271 --> 01:47.507
THESE OLD CHANDELIERS
ARE ALL ON THE SAME CIRCUIT.

01:47.507 --> 01:52.012
IF ONE BULB GOES OUT,
THEY ALL GO OUT.

01:52.012 --> 01:54.548
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR TAKING CARE OF IT.

01:54.548 --> 01:56.216
I'LL JUST BE A MINUTE.

01:56.216 --> 01:57.718
TAKE YOUR TIME.

01:57.718 --> 02:00.687
SINCE NICK IS AWAY, I'M JUST
CURLING UP WITH A CLASSIC.

02:00.687 --> 02:03.056
HE HAS
SUCH AN AMAZING LIBRARY.

02:03.056 --> 02:05.125
WELL,
THAT BOOK BELONGED TO DAHLIA.

02:05.125 --> 02:06.627
I NOTICED.

02:06.627 --> 02:11.231
THIS HAS AN UNUSUAL INSCRIPTION
FROM ADRIAN POWELL.

02:11.231 --> 02:13.266
DIDN'T THE POWELLS
USED TO BE GOOD FRIENDS

02:13.266 --> 02:14.401
WITH DAHLIA
AND NICK?

02:14.401 --> 02:16.269
WHY DO YOU ASK?

02:16.269 --> 02:18.972
WELL, I KNOW THERE WAS SOME SORT
OF FALLING OUT.

02:18.972 --> 02:22.376
I WAS JUST CURIOUS
IF YOU KNEW...ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

02:22.376 --> 02:25.612
YOU'RE ASKING ME
TO GOSSIP?

02:25.612 --> 02:29.349
IT'S NOT GOSSIP UNLESS
SOMETHING SCANDALOUS HAPPENED.

02:30.417 --> 02:33.387
DID SOMETHING
SCANDALOUS HAPPEN?

02:33.387 --> 02:37.257
IT'S NONE OF MY BUSINESS...
NOR YOURS.

02:37.257 --> 02:43.397
I WAS JUST ASKING IF DAHLIA
WAS UNUSUALLY CLOSE WITH ADRIAN.

02:43.397 --> 02:44.998
I DON'T THINK SO.

02:44.998 --> 02:48.001
WELL, DID SHE HAVE
ANY OTHER GENTLEMEN FRIENDS?

02:48.001 --> 02:50.971
ONES THAT SHE SPENT
A LOT OF TIME WITH?

02:50.971 --> 02:52.572
WHAT ARE YOU IMPLYING?

02:52.572 --> 02:54.241
OH, COME ON,
OPAL.

02:54.241 --> 02:56.977
I KNOW
DAHLIA HAD AN AFFAIR!

02:56.977 --> 03:00.547
ALL I WANT TO KNOW IS,
WHO WAS IT WITH?

03:00.547 --> 03:02.749
WHAT?! AAH!

03:06.219 --> 03:09.222
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

03:13.326 --> 03:15.328
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

03:18.598 --> 03:20.000
<i>HOLA,</i> GLORIA.

03:20.000 --> 03:21.234
HEY, I'M MAKING
CHILAQUILES TONIGHT.

03:21.234 --> 03:23.170
WHAT DO YOU HAVE
IN THE WAY OF POBLANOS?

03:23.170 --> 03:25.038
LET ME CHECK.

03:27.274 --> 03:31.611
YOU KNOW, FOR CHILAQUILES,
YOU REALLY SHOULD USE SERRANOS.

03:31.611 --> 03:33.980
HUH?

03:33.980 --> 03:37.150
FORTUNATELY, THIS MARKET
HAS A TERRIFIC SELECTION.

03:37.150 --> 03:39.152
WHAT ARE YOU,
CUBAN?

03:39.152 --> 03:40.253
COLOMBIAN?

03:40.253 --> 03:41.988
ARGENTINEAN.

03:41.988 --> 03:43.657
OF COURSE.

03:43.657 --> 03:46.259
I SHOULD HAVE BEEN TIPPED OFF
BY THE SUPERIOR ATTITUDE.

03:46.259 --> 03:47.661
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:47.661 --> 03:50.997
I'M MEXICAN.
WE INVENTED CHILAQUILES.

03:50.997 --> 03:52.666
DIDN'T MEAN
TO OFFEND YOU.

03:52.666 --> 03:55.502
FEEL FREE TO USE A BLAND PEPPER
OF YOUR CHOOSING.

03:55.502 --> 03:56.636
[ SCOFFS ]

03:56.636 --> 03:58.438
MY CHILAQUILES
ARE NOT BLAND.

03:58.438 --> 04:01.174
IF YOU'RE USING POBLANOS,
THEY ARE.

04:01.174 --> 04:03.276
I KNOW SOME PEOPLE
HAVE MEDICAL CONDITIONS

04:03.276 --> 04:05.679
WHICH PREVENT THEM
FROM EATING GROWN-UP PEPPERS.

04:05.679 --> 04:07.380
NOTHING TO BE ASHAMED OF.

04:07.380 --> 04:10.383
FIRST OF ALL, I DO NOT
HAVE A MEDICAL CONDITION,

04:10.383 --> 04:14.121
AND I HAVE YET TO MEET
THE PEPPER THAT I CAN'T HANDLE.

04:14.121 --> 04:17.991
AH, IN THAT CASE...
TRY THE SERRANOS.

04:17.991 --> 04:19.126
YOU'RE ON.

04:19.126 --> 04:20.527
[ CRUNCHES ]

04:20.527 --> 04:22.529
OH, I-I DIDN'T MEAN
TO EAT IT NOW.

04:24.664 --> 04:25.732
ARE YOU OKAY?

04:27.367 --> 04:29.302
[ Raspy ]
YOU CALL THAT SPICY?

04:29.302 --> 04:30.971
[ COUGHS ]
DRINK THIS.

04:30.971 --> 04:32.372
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:32.372 --> 04:34.007
[ COUGHING ]

04:34.007 --> 04:35.375
YOU'RE CRAZY.
YOU KNOW THAT?

04:35.375 --> 04:37.511
THAT PROVES NOTHING.

04:37.511 --> 04:42.215
WHAT MAKES YOU SUCH A HOT-SHOT
ABOUT COOKING?

04:42.215 --> 04:44.151
[ COUGHING ]
SEE THIS?

04:47.387 --> 04:49.189
PLEASE.

04:49.189 --> 04:51.491
YOU READ ONE LOUSY COOKBOOK
AND NOW YOU'RE AN EXPERT?

04:51.491 --> 04:54.161
GLORIA, UH,
PUT THIS ON MY TAB.

04:54.161 --> 04:57.130
I'M BUYING A COPY
FOR MY PAL, UH...

04:57.130 --> 04:59.266
ZOILA. AND YOU DON'T
HAVE TO DO THAT.

04:59.266 --> 05:01.635
NO, SERIOUSLY.
YOU SHOULD READ IT.

05:01.635 --> 05:03.737
YOU MIGHT
LEARN SOMETHING.

05:18.718 --> 05:21.221
[ FOOTSTEPS ]

05:23.590 --> 05:25.525
SUCH A SAD FACE.

05:25.525 --> 05:26.993
WHAT'S WRONG?

05:26.993 --> 05:29.462
I CAN'T BELIEVE
SHE CHOSE HIM OVER ME.

05:31.131 --> 05:32.566
RELAX.
I TOLD YOU --

05:32.566 --> 05:34.367
I'M GONNA TAKE CARE OF IT.

05:34.367 --> 05:36.169
IT MIGHT BE
TOO LATE.

05:36.169 --> 05:38.471
I THINK SHE'S FALLING IN LOVE
WITH HIM.

05:38.471 --> 05:41.341
THEN I
SHOULD GET BUSY.

05:43.109 --> 05:45.111
I DON'T NEED YOU
TO DO THIS FOR ME.

05:45.111 --> 05:48.114
I'M REALLY DOING THIS
FOR VALENTINA.

05:48.114 --> 05:51.117
DON'T YOU THINK
SHE DESERVES THE BEST?

05:55.455 --> 05:57.591
ETHAN!

05:57.591 --> 06:00.327
THE POOL
LOOKS AMAZING.

06:00.327 --> 06:02.262
NOT A LEAF IN SIGHT.

06:02.262 --> 06:04.231
WHAT IS YOUR SECRET?

06:04.231 --> 06:06.132
WELL,
I TAKE THIS THING

06:06.132 --> 06:09.236
AND SCOOP THE LEAVES
UNTIL THERE'S NONE LEFT.

06:09.236 --> 06:11.972
AHH.
HOW DECEPTIVELY SIMPLE.

06:11.972 --> 06:13.106
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:13.106 --> 06:17.110
SO...
TELL ME ABOUT YOURSELF.

06:17.110 --> 06:19.980
I'M SURE YOU HAVE BIGGER PLANS
FOR YOUR LIFE

06:19.980 --> 06:21.248
THAN CLEANING POOLS.

06:21.248 --> 06:22.549
WELL,
I'M JUST DOING THIS

06:22.549 --> 06:24.751
TO MAKE SOME SPENDING MONEY
BEFORE COLLEGE.

06:24.751 --> 06:27.254
COLLEGE.
HOW WONDERFUL.

06:27.254 --> 06:29.122
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

06:29.122 --> 06:30.390
I'M NOT SURE YET.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.492
I-I GOT INTO USC
AND UCLA.

06:32.492 --> 06:35.228
NOTHING
A LITTLE FURTHER AWAY?

06:35.228 --> 06:38.298
WELL,
BROWN IS MY DREAM SCHOOL.

06:38.298 --> 06:40.700
REMIND ME.
WHERE IS BROWN, AGAIN?

06:40.700 --> 06:42.068
RHODE ISLAND.

06:42.068 --> 06:46.239
YES! BROWN.
WONDERFUL SCHOOL.

06:46.239 --> 06:49.476
YOU MUST GO THERE.
BROWN.

06:49.476 --> 06:52.245
THE PROBLEM IS THEY HAVEN'T
OFFICIALLY ACCEPTED ME YET.

06:52.245 --> 06:53.647
I'M ON THE WAIT LIST.

06:53.647 --> 06:56.283
STILL,
IT'S VERY PROMISING.

06:56.283 --> 06:57.384
NOT REALLY.

06:57.384 --> 06:58.985
WELL,
IT'S AN IVY LEAGUE COLLEGE,

06:58.985 --> 07:00.654
SO THE CHANCES
OF ME MAKING THE FINAL CUT

07:00.654 --> 07:02.155
ARE, YOU KNOW,
SLIM TO NONE.

07:02.155 --> 07:04.257
OH.
I'M NOT SWEATING IT, THOUGH.

07:04.257 --> 07:06.993
YOU KNOW, IT'LL ALL WORK OUT
THE WAY IT'S MEANT TO.

07:06.993 --> 07:08.295
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:08.295 --> 07:11.498
I THINK
YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.

07:23.977 --> 07:26.746
SO,
WHICH PURSE DO YOU LIKE?

07:26.746 --> 07:28.014
UH...THAT ONE.

07:28.014 --> 07:30.517
WRONG.
THIS ONE IS BETTER.

07:30.517 --> 07:31.518
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:31.518 --> 07:33.653
NOW...
PICK A BRACELET.

07:33.653 --> 07:36.122
I LIKE THIS SILVER.

07:36.122 --> 07:38.458
UNLESS I -- I DON'T.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.627
NO!
GO AHEAD. PUT IT ON.

07:40.627 --> 07:42.128
OKAY.
[ SIGHS ]

07:42.128 --> 07:43.263
THERE YOU GO.

07:43.263 --> 07:45.198
NOW WE'RE COOKING
WITH GAS.

07:45.198 --> 07:48.368
IT WAS SO SWEET OF YOU
TO HELP ME.

07:48.368 --> 07:51.004
HOW CAN I
EVER REPAY YOU?

07:51.004 --> 07:53.239
I CAN THINK OF ONE WAY.

07:53.239 --> 07:55.742
DADDY GAVE ME POWER OF ATTORNEY
AFTER HIS STROKE,

07:55.742 --> 07:58.645
SO I ASKED REGGIE TO HELP
TAKE CARE OF THE FINANCES.

07:58.645 --> 08:00.981
I'M SUPPOSED TO GET
A MONTHLY STATEMENT,

08:00.981 --> 08:02.549
BUT HE'S
TWO MONTHS BEHIND.

08:02.549 --> 08:04.184
I'LL REMIND HIM.

08:04.184 --> 08:05.652
AND THANKS AGAIN.

08:05.652 --> 08:07.520
DON'T MENTION IT.

08:07.520 --> 08:10.123
IT WAS FUN
TO HELP YOU GET DRESSED UP.

08:10.123 --> 08:11.391
IF I HAD KEPT MY GIRL,

08:11.391 --> 08:14.027
I PROBABLY WOULD HAVE
HELPED HER, TOO,

08:14.027 --> 08:16.129
GETTING READY
FOR DATES AND ALL.

08:16.129 --> 08:17.397
YOU MISS HER,
HUH?

08:17.397 --> 08:18.698
I DON'T KNOW.

08:18.698 --> 08:20.667
CAN YOU MISS SOMEONE
YOU ONLY MET FOR FIVE MINUTES?

08:20.667 --> 08:23.169
I THINK SO.

08:23.169 --> 08:24.738
WELL,
WHAT'S DONE IS DONE.

08:24.738 --> 08:26.373
LET'S LEAVE IT
AT THAT.

08:26.373 --> 08:27.707
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

08:27.707 --> 08:30.210
THAT'S PROBABLY REGGIE.
YOU BETTER GET GOING.

08:34.647 --> 08:38.418
MISS LUCINDA,
IT MIGHT NOT BE MY PLACE TO SAY,

08:38.418 --> 08:42.522
BUT...I THINK YOU WOULD HAVE
MADE A WONDERFUL MOTHER.

08:42.522 --> 08:45.658
YOU CAN SAY THAT
ANY TIME YOU WANT.

08:45.658 --> 08:47.227
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

08:52.298 --> 08:55.035
UH, CARMEN?

08:55.035 --> 08:57.437
DIDN'T MY UNCLE TELL YOU
TO CLEAN UP THIS MESS?

08:57.437 --> 08:59.706
I GOT BIGGER PROBLEMS
THAN A DIRTY KITCHEN.

08:59.706 --> 09:03.309
HEY, HOW GOOD ARE YOU
AT ENGLISH?

09:03.309 --> 09:06.112
SPEAKING IT RIGHT NOW
AND YOU SEEM TO UNDERSTAND ME.

09:06.112 --> 09:08.181
YOU STUDY POETRY,
RIGHT?

09:08.181 --> 09:09.516
WHY?

09:09.516 --> 09:11.518
THERE'S A SHOWCASE
AT THE PRIMROSE CLUB,

09:11.518 --> 09:13.186
AND I WAS INVITED
TO SING.

09:13.186 --> 09:14.521
COOL.

09:14.521 --> 09:17.991
BUT IT HAS TO BE
AN ORIGINAL SONG IN ENGLISH.

09:17.991 --> 09:19.692
AND I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU REALIZE THIS,

09:19.692 --> 09:21.661
BUT ENGLISH
IS NOT MY FIRST LANGUAGE.

09:21.661 --> 09:23.129
[ CHUCKLES ] SORRY.

09:23.129 --> 09:26.066
I-I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT POETRY OR LYRICS.

09:26.066 --> 09:27.534
YOU KNOW
HOW TO WRITE.

09:27.534 --> 09:29.636
I ALWAYS SEE YOU
SCRIBBLING STUFF ON THAT BOOK.

09:29.636 --> 09:32.105
UH,
THIS IS MY THERAPY JOURNAL.

09:32.105 --> 09:34.741
I'M SUPPOSED TO WRITE DOWN
HOW I FEEL.

09:34.741 --> 09:37.977
CAN'T YOU FEEL LIKE
HELPING ME WRITE A SONG?

09:37.977 --> 09:39.279
[ SIGHS ]

09:39.279 --> 09:42.549
CARMEN, THAT EGG ROLL'S
BEEN THERE SINCE TUESDAY.

09:42.549 --> 09:45.385
STOP BEING
SUCH A NEAT FREAK.

09:45.385 --> 09:48.455
THIS SONG IS MY CHANCE
TO IMPRESS IMPORTANT PEOPLE,

09:48.455 --> 09:52.058
THE KIND THAT CAN MAKE
MY DREAMS COME TRUE.

09:52.058 --> 09:54.661
THAT'S WHY
I'VE GOT TO FINISH IT.

09:54.661 --> 09:58.631
WELL...WOULD IT HELP
IF <i>I</i> CLEANED THE KITCHEN?

09:58.631 --> 10:00.500
YOU'RE MY HERO.

10:02.402 --> 10:03.636
HEY!

10:03.636 --> 10:06.372
DON'T LEAVE AN EGG ROLL
OVER THERE.

10:06.372 --> 10:08.108
THAT'S DISGUSTING.

10:08.108 --> 10:10.243
[ SCOFFS ]

10:11.578 --> 10:14.147
THANKS.

10:14.147 --> 10:15.648
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

10:15.648 --> 10:16.649
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:16.649 --> 10:19.085
YOU CAN THANK
MISS LUCINDA.

10:19.085 --> 10:21.387
SHE HELPED ME
GET DRESSED TONIGHT.

10:21.387 --> 10:22.989
WHY?
DID SHE NEED A FAVOR?

10:22.989 --> 10:24.624
SHE WANTED ME
TO REMIND YOU

10:24.624 --> 10:27.193
SHE NEEDS A COPY
OF THOSE FINANCIAL PAPERS.

10:27.193 --> 10:30.630
I TOLD HER
I'M BUSY RIGHT NOW.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.165
BUT SHE ASKED
WEEKS AGO.

10:32.165 --> 10:34.100
AND YOU TELL
THAT MANIPULATIVE WITCH

10:34.100 --> 10:36.236
I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO INDULGE HER PARANOIA.

10:36.236 --> 10:38.371
WE NEED
TO BE NICE TO HER.

10:38.371 --> 10:40.406
SHE'S HAD
SUCH A HARD LIFE.

10:40.406 --> 10:43.476
WHAT'S SO HARD ABOUT BEING 40
AND MOOCHING OFF YOUR FATHER?

10:43.476 --> 10:45.245
I'M TALKING ABOUT BEFORE,

10:45.245 --> 10:47.981
WHEN SHE GAVE THAT BABY UP
FOR ADOPTION.

10:47.981 --> 10:50.517
'CINDA TOLD YOU
ABOUT THAT?

10:50.517 --> 10:53.653
IT'S A TERRIBLE THING
TO BE WITHOUT YOUR CHILD.

10:53.653 --> 10:57.157
YOU KNOW,
I HAD AN IDEA.

10:57.157 --> 11:00.059
I WANT TO FIND
MISS LUCINDA'S DAUGHTER.

11:00.059 --> 11:01.694
WHAT?

11:01.694 --> 11:03.429
I COULD
BRING THEM TOGETHER.

11:03.429 --> 11:04.998
WOULDN'T THAT BE WONDERFUL?

11:04.998 --> 11:06.399
I'M NOT SURE.

11:06.399 --> 11:08.968
Y-YOU'D BE DREDGING UP
A LOT OF PAINFUL MEMORIES.

11:08.968 --> 11:12.238
UH, 'CINDA MIGHT GET MAD
WITH UNCLE KEN ALL OVER AGAIN.

11:12.238 --> 11:13.506
YOU'RE WRONG.

11:13.506 --> 11:15.975
ONCE MISS LUCINDA'S ABLE
TO HOLD HER CHILD,

11:15.975 --> 11:19.412
SHE WILL BE SO HAPPY, SHE
WON'T CARE ABOUT ANYTHING ELSE.

11:21.514 --> 11:24.384
THAT'S A GOOD POINT.

11:24.384 --> 11:26.986
YOU KNOW, IT WOULDN'T BE HARD
TO TRACK HER BABY DOWN.

11:26.986 --> 11:28.388
REALLY?

11:28.388 --> 11:29.656
YEAH. THE ADOPTION PAPERWORK
IS BURIED SOMEWHERE

11:29.656 --> 11:31.658
IN THE FAMILY'S FILES.

11:31.658 --> 11:33.459
I COULD DIG IT OUT.

11:33.459 --> 11:35.328
SO YOU'LL HELP ME?

11:35.328 --> 11:36.529
WHY NOT?

11:36.529 --> 11:39.098
THIS COULD BE
SO WONDERFUL!

11:39.098 --> 11:42.001
MISS LUCINDA
MEETING HER DAUGHTER!

11:42.001 --> 11:45.038
CAN YOU IMAGINE
THE LOOK ON HER FACE?

11:45.038 --> 11:47.173
I CAN.

11:47.173 --> 11:49.309
I ABSOLUTELY CAN.

12:01.554 --> 12:03.756
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
YOU WERE A WORLD-FAMOUS CHEF?

12:03.756 --> 12:05.525
[ CHUCKLES ]
I DON'T KNOW.

12:05.525 --> 12:08.228
SOMETIMES, I GET NERVOUS
AROUND PRETTY WOMEN.

12:08.228 --> 12:10.563
YOU THINK
I'M PRETTY?

12:10.563 --> 12:11.698
NICE.

12:11.698 --> 12:13.600
DID YOU READ
MY BOOK?

12:13.600 --> 12:15.101
COVER TO COVER.

12:15.101 --> 12:17.237
AT FIRST, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE THIS MACHO JERK

12:17.237 --> 12:20.340
TRYING TO PUSH ME AROUND, BUT...
YOU SEEM TO KNOW YOUR STUFF.

12:20.340 --> 12:22.141
SO YOU THINK
I'M MACHO?

12:22.141 --> 12:23.743
NICE.

12:23.743 --> 12:28.114
ANYWAY, I DECIDED TO GIVE <i>YOUR</i>
RECIPE FOR CHILAQUILES A TRY,

12:28.114 --> 12:29.549
SERRANOS INCLUDED.

12:29.549 --> 12:32.118
AND YOU WERE...
BLOWN AWAY?

12:32.118 --> 12:33.286
[ LAUGHS ]

12:33.286 --> 12:36.456
SWEETIE,
NOT BY A LONG SHOT.

12:39.259 --> 12:40.593
WHAT'S THIS?

12:40.593 --> 12:42.395
<i>MY</i> CHILAQUILES.

12:42.395 --> 12:45.331
YOU CAME ALL THE WAY DOWN HERE
TO MAKE ME TRY YOUR RECIPE?

12:45.331 --> 12:46.399
GO ON.

12:46.399 --> 12:48.968
YOU MIGHT
LEARN SOMETHING.

12:48.968 --> 12:51.004
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:55.108 --> 12:57.176
OH, MY GOD.

12:57.176 --> 12:59.379
THIS IS FANTASTIC.

12:59.379 --> 13:00.680
UH-HUH.

13:00.680 --> 13:03.349
I'M GETTING THE OREGANO,
THE CILANTRO, BUT...

13:03.349 --> 13:04.384
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE.

13:04.384 --> 13:05.652
CAN'T PUT YOUR FINGER
ON IT?

13:05.652 --> 13:07.387
NO.
WHAT IS IT?

13:07.387 --> 13:09.222
NICE TRY.

13:09.222 --> 13:10.390
[ LAUGHS ] OKAY.

13:10.390 --> 13:12.258
TRADE SECRET.
I GET IT.

13:12.258 --> 13:14.994
YOU'VE CERTAINLY
DAZZLED MY PALATE.

13:14.994 --> 13:16.629
LET ME
RETURN THE FAVOR.

13:16.629 --> 13:18.264
COME TO MY HOUSE TONIGHT.

13:18.264 --> 13:19.999
I'LL MAKE DINNER
FOR YOU.

13:19.999 --> 13:24.270
WOULD THIS BE LIKE...
A DATE?

13:24.270 --> 13:25.605
ABSOLUTELY.

13:25.605 --> 13:27.507
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

13:27.507 --> 13:29.609
NUTMEG.

13:29.609 --> 13:31.277
HMM?

13:31.277 --> 13:33.012
THE SECRET INGREDIENT
IS NUTMEG.

13:33.012 --> 13:34.981
AH.

13:34.981 --> 13:36.482
STILL WANT ME
TO COME OVER?

13:36.482 --> 13:38.584
OF COURSE.
WHY?

13:38.584 --> 13:41.487
JUST CHECKING.

13:46.092 --> 13:47.460
HELLO, MARISOL.

13:47.460 --> 13:49.162
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

13:49.162 --> 13:50.997
THEY'RE KEEPING ME
FOR A FEW DAYS

13:50.997 --> 13:52.432
TO SEE
IF I HAVE BRAIN DAMAGE.

13:52.432 --> 13:55.401
IF I START TO DROOL,
CALL A DOCTOR.

13:55.401 --> 13:59.539
YOU'RE MAKING JOKES.
THAT'S GOOD!

13:59.539 --> 14:01.541
I WAS REALLY WORRIED
ABOUT YOU.

14:01.541 --> 14:03.142
AS WELL
YOU SHOULD BE.

14:03.142 --> 14:04.677
YOU'RE THE REASON
I FELL.

14:04.677 --> 14:07.180
NO, NOT TRUE.

14:07.180 --> 14:10.249
YOU MAY HAVE GOTTEN DISTRACTED
WHILE I WAS TALKING.

14:10.249 --> 14:13.252
YOU WERE SPEWING VILE RUMORS
ABOUT A DEAD WOMAN,

14:13.252 --> 14:14.454
TRYING TO SHOCK ME.

14:14.454 --> 14:16.522
NOW,
THAT'S JUST SILLY.

14:16.522 --> 14:18.257
I DON'T THINK SO.

14:18.257 --> 14:20.693
AND NEITHER
WILL NICHOLAS.

14:22.362 --> 14:24.364
WHAT?

14:24.364 --> 14:27.533
HE'S GOING TO ASK
WHAT HAPPENED.

14:27.533 --> 14:29.969
I DON'T LIKE
TO LIE.

14:29.969 --> 14:33.039
SO...WHAT?

14:33.039 --> 14:34.540
ARE YOU GONNA TATTLE
ON ME?

14:34.540 --> 14:38.077
I GUESS
I DON'T <i>HAVE TO.</i>

14:38.077 --> 14:42.115
OF COURSE,
I WOULD LIKE A FAVOR IN RETURN.

14:42.115 --> 14:43.282
WHAT'S THAT?

14:43.282 --> 14:45.551
A PROMISE
TO NOT DISCUSS DAHLIA

14:45.551 --> 14:49.055
OR HER EXTRACURRICULAR
ACTIVITIES WITH ANYONE.

14:49.055 --> 14:52.625
SHE MAY BE DEAD, BUT I STILL
PROTECT HER REPUTATION.

14:52.625 --> 14:55.461
FINE.

14:55.461 --> 14:57.563
I DON'T REALLY CARE.

14:57.563 --> 15:02.201
I WAS JUST...
CURIOUS.

15:02.201 --> 15:04.036
SO WAS THE CAT.

15:05.338 --> 15:08.641
WE ALL KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM.

15:08.641 --> 15:10.610
[ SCOFFS ]

15:12.412 --> 15:13.679
[ DOOR OPENS ]

15:13.679 --> 15:15.648
YOU'LL NEVER GUESS
WHAT HAPPENED.

15:15.648 --> 15:17.984
GO ON. GUESS.

15:17.984 --> 15:19.986
NO, FORGET IT.
I'LL JUST TELL YOU.

15:19.986 --> 15:21.187
I GOT INTO BROWN.

15:21.187 --> 15:22.655
[ LAUGHS ] YOU DID?!

15:22.655 --> 15:25.024
YEP. JUST GOT AN E-MAIL
ABOUT 20 MINUTES AGO.

15:25.024 --> 15:26.426
I'M OFF
THE WAIT LIST.

15:26.426 --> 15:27.660
OH!
THAT'S AMAZING.

15:27.660 --> 15:29.295
MWAH!
I KNOW.
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

15:29.295 --> 15:31.264
AND I WAS JUST TALKING
TO MRS. DELATOUR YESTERDAY

15:31.264 --> 15:32.999
ABOUT HOW HARD IT IS
TO GET IN.

15:32.999 --> 15:34.367
MRS. DELATOUR?
YEAH.

15:34.367 --> 15:35.735
SHE WAS ASKING ME
ABOUT MY COLLEGE PLANS.

15:35.735 --> 15:39.172
AND YOU TOLD HER
YOU WANTED TO GO TO BROWN?

15:39.172 --> 15:41.240
CLEAR YOUR NIGHT,

15:41.240 --> 15:44.243
BECAUSE WE ARE DOING
SOME SERIOUS CELEBRATING.

15:45.678 --> 15:47.713
[ SIGHS ]

15:51.350 --> 15:52.385
[ DOOR OPENS ]

15:54.053 --> 15:55.121
I DON'T GET IT.

15:55.121 --> 15:56.989
OPAL HAS BEEN SO NASTY
TO YOU.

15:56.989 --> 15:58.624
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO
BRING HER CLOTHES?

15:58.624 --> 16:01.093
EVEN BITCHES NEED SOMETHING
TO WEAR HOME FROM THE HOSPITAL.

16:02.528 --> 16:05.031
CARMEN,
GET AWAY FROM THERE.

16:05.031 --> 16:06.365
BUT I LOVE
GOING THROUGH PEOPLE'S STUFF.

16:06.365 --> 16:07.967
I KNOW.
BUT IF OPAL FINDS OUT...

16:07.967 --> 16:09.268
[ GASPS ]

16:09.268 --> 16:10.970
WHAT IS IT?

16:10.970 --> 16:14.474
LOOK AT
ALL THESE UGLY SHOES!

16:14.474 --> 16:15.641
OPAL'S A MAID.

16:15.641 --> 16:17.543
SHE LIKES
TO BE COMFORTABLE.

16:17.543 --> 16:20.246
YEAH, WELL, 10 PAIRS
OF BLACK LOAFERS? COME ON!

16:20.246 --> 16:24.517
YOU KNOW, ONCE I GET THIS BAG
PACKED, I'M SENDING YOU HOME.

16:24.517 --> 16:26.118
[ DRAWER RATTLES ]

16:26.118 --> 16:27.253
IS IT STUCK?

16:27.253 --> 16:29.021
I THINK
IT'S LOCKED.

16:29.021 --> 16:30.389
OOH.

16:30.389 --> 16:33.025
WHAT DO YOU THINK
IS IN THERE?

16:33.025 --> 16:34.227
I DON'T KNOW.

16:34.227 --> 16:36.295
IS IT AWFUL
THAT I'M CURIOUS?

16:36.295 --> 16:37.396
NO!

16:37.396 --> 16:38.564
YOU WANT
TO LOOK FOR A KEY?

16:38.564 --> 16:40.366
CAN'T YOU
JUST PICK THE LOCK?

16:40.366 --> 16:42.068
WHY WOULD YOU
SAY THAT?

16:42.068 --> 16:44.103
IS IT
BECAUSE I'M PUERTO RICAN?

16:44.103 --> 16:46.372
BECAUSE THAT'S RACIST.
I AM SO SORRY.

16:46.372 --> 16:48.508
I DIDN'T MEAN
TO OFFEND YOU.

16:48.508 --> 16:50.109
HOW COULD I
OFFEND YOU --

16:50.109 --> 16:51.177
WE'RE IN.

16:51.177 --> 16:52.645
A NEGLIGEE?
HUH.

16:52.645 --> 16:55.414
WHY WOULD OPAL
LOCK UP A NEGLIGEE?

16:55.414 --> 16:57.650
WHY WOULD SHE LOCK UP
ANY OF THIS STUFF?

16:57.650 --> 16:59.986
THERE'S A MENU, A SCARF,
TICKET STUBS.

16:59.986 --> 17:01.587
THERE'S A PICTURE
OF A BLONDE.

17:03.222 --> 17:05.424
THAT'S DAHLIA.

17:05.424 --> 17:06.626
OH.

17:06.626 --> 17:08.628
OH, MY GOD,
MARISOL.

17:08.628 --> 17:10.563
THERE'S A LOT
OF THEM.

17:10.563 --> 17:11.697
WHAT?

17:11.697 --> 17:14.567
I...
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

17:14.567 --> 17:15.968
<i>¿QUé TE PASA?</i>

17:15.968 --> 17:18.371
NICK SAID
SHE HAD AN AFFAIR.

17:18.371 --> 17:20.740
WHY COULDN'T IT BE
WITH HER?

17:20.740 --> 17:22.575
ARE YOU SAYING
THAT OPAL'S A LESBIAN?

17:22.575 --> 17:25.244
IT WOULD CERTAINLY EXPLAIN
THE UGLY SHOES.

17:39.413 --> 17:40.715
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

17:40.715 --> 17:42.316
CARMEN CALLED.

17:42.316 --> 17:44.385
SHE TOLD US ABOUT
THE SECRET LESBIAN DRAWER.

17:44.385 --> 17:45.686
WHERE IS IT?

17:49.890 --> 17:52.493
SO, YOU FOUND ALL THIS STUFF
IN OPAL'S DRAWER?

17:52.493 --> 17:55.463
I'M THINKING THEY'RE MEMENTOS
FROM HER AFFAIR WITH DAHLIA.

17:55.463 --> 17:57.331
HER <i>LESBIAN</i> AFFAIR.

17:57.331 --> 17:58.499
YES.

17:58.499 --> 18:00.534
SORRY I WASN'T
MORE SPECIFIC.

18:00.534 --> 18:02.503
YOU KNOW,
LESBIANS WORSHIP ME.

18:02.503 --> 18:03.771
HAVE I MENTIONED THAT?

18:03.771 --> 18:06.273
NO, THAT'S A SENTENCE
I'D REMEMBER.

18:06.273 --> 18:07.808
IT'S TRUE.

18:07.808 --> 18:10.344
I CANNOT GO TO A HARDWARE STORE
WITHOUT GETTING HIT ON.

18:10.344 --> 18:12.379
I THOUGHT IT WAS KOREANS
WHO WORSHIPPED YOU.

18:12.379 --> 18:14.415
I AM POPULAR
WITH BOTH KOREANS AND LESBIANS.

18:14.415 --> 18:16.517
IS THERE ANYONE
WHO DOESN'T LIKE YOU?

18:16.517 --> 18:17.918
BESIDES ME?

18:17.918 --> 18:20.521
YOU KNOW, IN A WAY, I'M RELIEVED
I FOUND THIS DRAWER.

18:20.521 --> 18:23.457
IT EXPLAINS EVERYTHING THAT'S
HAPPENED SINCE I MOVED HERE.

18:23.457 --> 18:25.292
IF OPAL
HAD AN AFFAIR WITH DAHLIA,

18:25.292 --> 18:26.894
NO WONDER NICK
IS SO UNCOMFORTABLE.

18:26.894 --> 18:28.562
BUT THAT'S WHAT BOTHERS ME.

18:28.562 --> 18:31.532
IF NICK KNOWS HIS WIFE
AND HIS MAID WERE LOVERS...

18:31.532 --> 18:35.436
WHY IS SHE
STILL WORKING HERE?

18:35.436 --> 18:38.572
IT'S SO LOVELY OF YOU
TO DROP BY.

18:38.572 --> 18:41.675
I WANTED TO SHARE
SOME GOOD NEWS.

18:41.675 --> 18:43.644
ETHAN GOT INTO BROWN.

18:43.644 --> 18:47.248
ETHAN TOLD ME
HE WAS HOPING THAT WOULD HAPPEN

18:47.248 --> 18:48.682
JUST THE OTHER DAY.

18:48.682 --> 18:49.784
YES.

18:49.784 --> 18:52.186
IT'S QUITE
THE COINCIDENCE.

18:52.186 --> 18:54.688
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S WONDERFUL FOR HIM.

18:54.688 --> 18:57.458
BUT SAD
FOR MY POOL.

18:57.458 --> 18:59.360
HUH?

18:59.360 --> 19:02.797
ETHAN CAN'T BE MY POOL BOY
ONCE HE'S IN RHODE ISLAND.

19:02.797 --> 19:05.366
HE COULD TRY
TO LOOK AFTER IT,

19:05.366 --> 19:08.669
BUT LONG-DISTANCE RELATIONSHIPS
ARE SO HARD.

19:08.669 --> 19:10.871
AND POOLS HAVE NEEDS.

19:10.871 --> 19:13.874
CAN'T YOU JUST
FIND SOMEONE ELSE?

19:13.874 --> 19:15.276
YES.

19:15.276 --> 19:17.645
AND YOU KNOW
WHO IT SHOULD BE?

19:17.645 --> 19:18.913
MY FIRST POOL BOY.

19:18.913 --> 19:21.916
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY I LET HIM GO.

19:21.916 --> 19:26.353
TRUE, HE MADE A FEW MISTAKES,
BUT I'M SURE HE'S VERY SORRY.

19:26.353 --> 19:29.824
MRS. DELATOUR, I'M NOT
GETTING BACK TOGETHER WITH REMI.

19:29.824 --> 19:32.193
WHO SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT REMI?

19:33.494 --> 19:35.396
ALTHOUGH,
NOW THAT YOU BRING IT UP --

19:35.396 --> 19:36.630
STOP.

19:36.630 --> 19:39.133
I KNOW
THAT YOU GOT ETHAN INTO BROWN.

19:39.133 --> 19:40.668
WHAT?!

19:40.668 --> 19:44.905
NOW I NEED YOU TO TELL ME,
DID REMI PUT YOU UP TO IT?

19:47.541 --> 19:50.377
NO.
IT WAS ALL ME.

19:50.377 --> 19:53.280
WHY WOULD YOU
DO THAT?

19:53.280 --> 19:57.918
SINCE THE MOMENT YOU FIRST TOLD
ME YOU WERE IN LOVE WITH REMI,

19:57.918 --> 20:01.222
I KNEW HE'D NEVER
FIND ANYONE BETTER.

20:01.222 --> 20:04.792
AND I ALSO THOUGHT
IF YOU TWO GOT MARRIED,

20:04.792 --> 20:08.896
THEN YOU AND YOUR MOTHER
WOULDN'T BE <i>LIKE</i> FAMILY ANYMORE.

20:08.896 --> 20:10.397
YOU'D <i>BE</i> FAMILY.

20:12.466 --> 20:15.369
AND I STILL WANT THAT
SO VERY MUCH.

20:15.369 --> 20:18.806
MRS. DELATOUR, I LOVE YOU,
AND I ALWAYS WILL.

20:18.806 --> 20:21.242
YOU'VE BEEN A SECOND MOTHER
TO ME MY WHOLE LIFE.

20:21.242 --> 20:22.776
REALLY?

20:22.776 --> 20:27.815
THAT'S WHY I FEEL I CAN TELL YOU
WHAT I TELL MY REAL MOM --

20:27.815 --> 20:29.149
BUTT OUT.

20:36.757 --> 20:39.360
♪ I'M STILL TRYING ♪

20:39.360 --> 20:41.562
[ KEYBOARD PLAYS ]

20:41.562 --> 20:47.368
♪ AND ALMOST CRYING ♪

20:47.368 --> 20:51.505
♪ WHILE THE LAUNDRY'S DRYING ♪

20:51.505 --> 20:52.640
WHAT THE -- [ SIGHS ]

20:52.640 --> 20:54.475
STUPID ENGLISH.

20:54.475 --> 20:56.143
[ DRYER BUZZES ]

21:14.228 --> 21:16.397
WHOOPS.

21:28.175 --> 21:31.211
SON OF A BITCH!

21:31.211 --> 21:33.447
YOU HAVE A DATE?

21:33.447 --> 21:35.582
I'M SO EXCITED!

21:35.582 --> 21:36.583
WHY?

21:36.583 --> 21:38.385
IT'S MY DATE,
NOT YOURS.

21:38.385 --> 21:39.920
SO,
WHERE'S HE TAKING YOU?

21:39.920 --> 21:42.623
TO HIS HOUSE.
HE'S MAKING ME DINNER.

21:42.623 --> 21:43.891
OH.

21:43.891 --> 21:46.360
I WANTED
TO BRING DESSERT,

21:46.360 --> 21:48.495
BUT JAVIER WROTE A BOOK
ABOUT FRENCH PASTRY.

21:48.495 --> 21:50.698
WILL HE REALLY WANT
TO SAMPLE <i>MY</i> BUNDT CAKE?

21:50.698 --> 21:53.467
HE'LL WANT TO SAMPLE
MORE THAN THAT.

21:53.467 --> 21:55.269
HUH?

21:55.269 --> 21:59.406
WHEN A MAN COOKS FOR YOU,
HE EXPECTS SOMETHING IN RETURN.

22:01.475 --> 22:03.510
GOD!
I'M SUCH AN IDIOT!

22:03.510 --> 22:06.847
I WAS SO JAZZED A CUTE GUY
WANTED TO SPEND TIME WITH ME,

22:06.847 --> 22:11.151
I DIDN'T EVEN THINK ABOUT...
GETTING PHYSICAL.

22:11.151 --> 22:13.821
[ GROANS ]

22:13.821 --> 22:18.726
HONEY, YOU WERE MARRIED
FOR 22 YEARS.

22:18.726 --> 22:23.664
IT'S ONLY NATURAL YOU'D FORGET
THAT PEOPLE HAVE SEX.

22:40.514 --> 22:41.915
EXCUSE ME.

22:41.915 --> 22:44.885
ARE YOU NATASHA JONES?

22:44.885 --> 22:46.854
YEAH.

22:46.854 --> 22:49.323
YOU WERE ADOPTED,
RIGHT?

22:49.323 --> 22:51.759
WHY WOULD YOU
ASK ME THAT?

22:51.759 --> 22:56.196
THERE IS SOMEONE
WHO'D LIKE TO MEET YOU.

22:59.700 --> 23:02.136
[ DOOR OPENS ]

23:06.373 --> 23:08.509
YOU MUST BE ETHAN.
I'M --

23:08.509 --> 23:10.144
I KNOW
WHO YOU ARE.

23:10.144 --> 23:13.180
YOUR MOM SAID I COULD
HELP MYSELF TO A SODA.

23:13.180 --> 23:14.515
SURE.

23:14.515 --> 23:16.517
GO AHEAD.

23:18.552 --> 23:21.522
NAH.
I'LL COME BACK.

23:21.522 --> 23:23.657
LOOK, THIS DOESN'T
HAVE TO BE AWKWARD.

23:23.657 --> 23:24.725
[ SCOFFS ]

23:24.725 --> 23:26.360
I DIDN'T THINK
IT WAS.

23:26.360 --> 23:27.628
GOOD.

23:27.628 --> 23:29.463
VALENTINA AND I
ARE STILL FRIENDS,

23:29.463 --> 23:32.733
SO YOU AND I ARE BOUND TO RUN
INTO EACH OTHER OCCASIONALLY.

23:32.733 --> 23:38.138
UNLESS I SHIP OFF TO BROWN,
RIGHT?

23:38.138 --> 23:40.374
EXCUSE ME?

23:40.374 --> 23:42.376
I JUST GOT
MY ACCEPTANCE LETTER.

23:42.376 --> 23:45.813
HOW MANY BUILDINGS DID YOUR MOM
HAVE TO BUY TO MAKE THAT HAPPEN?

23:47.514 --> 23:49.917
[ SCOFFS ]
OH, MAN.

23:49.917 --> 23:51.919
LOOK, I'M --
I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

23:51.919 --> 23:53.821
MY MOM'S ALWAYS TRYING
TO HELP ME OUT, AND...

23:53.821 --> 23:55.923
SOMETIMES,
SHE GOES TOO FAR.

23:55.923 --> 23:57.825
WELL,
I'M NOT GOING FAR.

23:57.825 --> 23:59.760
I'M STAYING
RIGHT HERE.

23:59.760 --> 24:01.195
REALLY?

24:01.195 --> 24:02.229
YEAH.

24:02.229 --> 24:04.198
YOU SEE,
I'M NOT SOME PROBLEM

24:04.198 --> 24:06.300
THAT YOU CAN BUY YOUR WAY
OUT OF.

24:06.300 --> 24:08.669
LOOK, I WAS JUST TRYING
TO BE FRIENDLY,

24:08.669 --> 24:11.738
BUT YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY
NOT INTERESTED IN THAT, SO...

24:13.507 --> 24:15.409
THIS MUST REALLY BURN.

24:17.277 --> 24:19.813
RICH KID LOSING
TO THE POOL BOY.

24:19.813 --> 24:22.716
YOU SEEM KIND OF OBSESSED
WITH OTHER PEOPLE'S MONEY.

24:22.716 --> 24:25.486
HEY,
I GOT WHAT I WANT.

24:25.486 --> 24:31.458
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME, SOME
OF US HAVE TO WORK FOR A LIVING.

24:32.593 --> 24:33.894
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

24:33.894 --> 24:36.597
WERE YOU TALKING
TO SOMEONE?

24:36.597 --> 24:37.898
YEAH.

24:37.898 --> 24:40.667
I JUST MET ETHAN.

24:40.667 --> 24:41.869
OH.

24:41.869 --> 24:44.471
HOW DID THAT GO?

24:44.471 --> 24:45.539
GOOD.

24:45.539 --> 24:48.175
HELPED ME
REALIZE SOMETHING --

24:48.175 --> 24:49.443
YOU WERE RIGHT.

24:49.443 --> 24:52.913
VALENTINA
DOES DESERVE THE BEST.

24:52.913 --> 24:56.216
AND THAT PIECE OF CRAP
DOESN'T EVEN COME CLOSE.

25:00.587 --> 25:02.556
YOU'RE A LIAR.

25:02.556 --> 25:03.891
EXCUSE ME?

25:03.891 --> 25:06.160
YOU SAID YOU DIDN'T KNOW
HOW TO WRITE LYRICS.

25:06.160 --> 25:07.327
I DON'T.

25:07.327 --> 25:08.795
HA! MORE LIES.

25:08.795 --> 25:12.399
BUT YOU SAVED MY CAREER,
SO I FORGIVE YOU.

25:14.368 --> 25:15.903
WHAT'S THIS?

25:15.903 --> 25:17.504
JUST LISTEN.

25:19.139 --> 25:23.477
♪ IN MY ROOM
LATE AT NIGHT ♪

25:23.477 --> 25:24.811
WAIT A MINUTE.

25:24.811 --> 25:29.416
♪ I THINK OF YOU
AND YOUR SAD EYES ♪

25:29.416 --> 25:31.785
OH, MY GOD!
YOU READ MY JOURNAL?!

25:31.785 --> 25:33.520
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE LEFT IT
ON TOP OF THE BED

25:33.520 --> 25:35.222
WHERE DESPERATE PEOPLE
COULD GET TO IT.

25:35.222 --> 25:36.523
WHAT ELSE
DID YOU READ?

25:36.523 --> 25:37.891
NOTHING.
JUST THAT ONE PAGE.

25:37.891 --> 25:39.459
AND YOU DIDN'T READ
ANYTHING ELSE?

25:39.459 --> 25:40.594
NO.

25:42.262 --> 25:43.664
I DIDN'T STEAL
ALL OF THE POEM,

25:43.664 --> 25:45.232
AND I ADDED WORDS
OF MY OWN.

25:45.232 --> 25:46.366
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

25:46.366 --> 25:48.268
THIS IS
SUCH A VIOLATION.

25:48.268 --> 25:49.870
I'M SURE
YOU'LL FEEL DIFFERENTLY

25:49.870 --> 25:51.638
ONCE THE SONG
BECOMES A BIG HIT.

25:51.638 --> 25:53.307
WAIT.

25:53.307 --> 25:55.375
YOU THINK YOU'RE GONNA SING THIS
IN FRONT OF PEOPLE?

25:55.375 --> 25:56.543
SURE.

25:56.543 --> 25:58.312
I MEAN,
THE SHOWCASE IS TONIGHT.

25:58.312 --> 25:59.913
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

25:59.913 --> 26:03.517
IF YOU SING MY WORDS
IN PUBLIC,

26:03.517 --> 26:05.485
I WILL TELL MY UNCLE
THAT YOU WENT THROUGH MY STUFF

26:05.485 --> 26:08.255
AND THAT YOU WRITE MUSIC
WHEN YOU SHOULD BE WORKING,

26:08.255 --> 26:10.357
AND I WILL GET YOU FIRED
FROM THIS JOB.

26:10.357 --> 26:11.391
DO YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

26:11.391 --> 26:12.893
TY,
TAKE IT EASY.

26:12.893 --> 26:14.261
LOOK, DO YOU
UNDERSTAND ME?!

26:24.504 --> 26:28.242
MISS LUCINDA, THERE IS SOMEONE
HERE TO SEE YOU.

26:28.242 --> 26:30.444
TELL THEM I'M BUSY.

26:30.444 --> 26:31.612
OH, NO.

26:31.612 --> 26:33.780
YOU'LL WANT
TO STOP FOR THIS.

26:45.626 --> 26:47.628
WHO IS THIS?

26:47.628 --> 26:49.630
YOUR DAUGHTER.

26:49.630 --> 26:51.265
WHAT?

26:51.265 --> 26:55.636
I FOUND HER
FOR YOU.

26:55.636 --> 26:57.671
NATASHA,
THIS IS YOUR MOTHER.

26:57.671 --> 26:59.439
OH,
MY LORD.

26:59.439 --> 27:02.743
WE CONTACTED
THE ADOPTION AGENCY.

27:02.743 --> 27:04.411
THEY HELPED US.

27:04.411 --> 27:06.913
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

27:06.913 --> 27:11.485
I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D SEE YOU AGAIN.

27:11.485 --> 27:15.188
COME HERE,
BABY GIRL.

27:20.560 --> 27:23.397
[ GASPS ]

27:31.805 --> 27:34.641
I'M NOT
A TERRIBLE PERSON.

27:34.641 --> 27:40.147
BUT I WANT A CAREER SO MUCH,
SOMETIMES I DO TERRIBLE THINGS.

27:40.147 --> 27:45.652
TY, I DIDN'T MEAN
TO INVADE YOUR PRIVACY.

27:45.652 --> 27:48.655
I JUST SAW THESE WORDS ON
A PAGE, AND THEY SPOKE TO ME.

27:48.655 --> 27:52.726
WHAT YOU WROTE ABOUT DARKNESS
AND TRYING TO FIND THE LIGHT,

27:52.726 --> 27:56.897
IT'S LIKE YOU FOUND <i>MY</i> JOURNAL
AND YOU READ WHAT WAS INSIDE.

27:56.897 --> 28:00.634
YOU DESCRIBE HOW I FELT
AFTER ALEJANDRO WAS KILLED.

28:00.634 --> 28:06.640
I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE TO PUT IT
INTO WORDS, BUT YOU DID.

28:06.640 --> 28:07.908
STILL...

28:07.908 --> 28:12.145
I WON'T SING THE SONG
IF YOU DON'T WANT ME TO.

28:12.145 --> 28:15.882
[ SIGHS ]

28:20.887 --> 28:23.256
OKAY.

28:24.324 --> 28:26.326
OKAY?

28:27.761 --> 28:32.899
YOU CAN SING THE SONG
THIS ONE TIME.

28:32.899 --> 28:35.369
SERIOUSLY?

28:35.369 --> 28:37.838
TY, THANK YOU.

28:37.838 --> 28:39.806
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING TONIGHT?

28:39.806 --> 28:41.508
I CAN'T GO
TO THE SHOWCASE.

28:41.508 --> 28:43.243
IT'D BE
TOO EMBARRASSING.

28:43.243 --> 28:46.179
BUT DON'T YOU WANT TO SEE PEOPLE
ENJOYING <i>YOUR</i> WORDS?

28:46.179 --> 28:47.781
I DON'T THINK SO.

28:47.781 --> 28:52.652
BUT AFTER THE SHOW, COME BACK
AND TELL ME HOW YOU DID.

28:52.652 --> 28:57.457
SINCE YOU WON'T BE THERE,
I'LL TELL YOU AHEAD OF TIME.

28:57.457 --> 29:00.160
I WAS GREAT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:00.160 --> 29:02.329
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

29:02.329 --> 29:04.364
WHY WOULD YOU
DO THIS?

29:04.364 --> 29:05.766
SHE IS YOUR MOTHER.

29:05.766 --> 29:07.601
MY MOTHER
IS A NURSE IN RESEDA.

29:07.601 --> 29:10.771
SHE SPENT 20 YEARS WORKING HER
ASS OFF TO GIVE ME AN EDUCATION.

29:10.771 --> 29:12.706
THIS RICH BITCH
IS NOTHING TO ME.

29:12.706 --> 29:15.275
NATASHA!
IT'S OKAY, ROSIE.

29:15.275 --> 29:18.145
SHE HAS EVERY RIGHT
TO HATE ME.

29:18.145 --> 29:20.814
I ABANDONED HER.

29:20.814 --> 29:25.919
BUT YOU HAVE TO KNOW,
I NEVER STOPPED LOVING YOU.

29:25.919 --> 29:29.156
THEN WHY DIDN'T YOU WANT TO
SEE ME THE LAST TIME I WAS HERE?

29:29.156 --> 29:31.425
LAST TIME?

29:31.425 --> 29:33.527
FOUR YEARS AGO.

29:33.527 --> 29:35.629
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

29:35.629 --> 29:37.397
I WENT THROUGH
THIS PHASE,

29:37.397 --> 29:39.900
THOUGHT I WANTED TO KNOW
WHERE I CAME FROM.

29:39.900 --> 29:41.902
SO I HIRED
A PRIVATE DETECTIVE.

29:41.902 --> 29:44.771
HE TRACKED YOU DOWN.
BUT WHEN I CAME HERE
AND ASKED TO MEET YOU,

29:44.771 --> 29:47.774
YOUR FATHER TOLD ME YOU DIDN'T
WANT ANYTHING TO DO WITH ME.

29:47.774 --> 29:49.276
HE DID WHAT?

29:49.276 --> 29:52.379
MR. KENNETH
WOULDN'T SAY THAT.

29:52.379 --> 29:53.513
WOULD HE?

29:53.513 --> 29:55.415
OF COURSE HE WOULD.

29:56.883 --> 29:59.319
YOU DIDN'T KNOW?

29:59.319 --> 30:02.222
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

30:04.224 --> 30:06.326
OH, MY GOD.

30:09.362 --> 30:12.499
ALL THIS TIME, I-I THOUGHT
YOU JUST DIDN'T WANT TO SEE ME.

30:12.499 --> 30:15.469
WHEN THEY GRABBED YOU
AWAY FROM ME,

30:15.469 --> 30:17.904
THEY TOOK A PIECE
OF MY SOUL.

30:17.904 --> 30:20.373
BUT NOW
I'VE GOT IT BACK.

30:21.842 --> 30:25.512
AND WE DON'T NEED
TEARS ANYMORE.

30:25.512 --> 30:28.215
WE ARE HAPPY PEOPLE.

30:32.452 --> 30:33.587
SEE?

30:33.587 --> 30:34.921
EVERYTHING WORKED OUT
FOR THE BEST.

30:37.491 --> 30:39.226
IT DID.

30:40.627 --> 30:46.366
NOW, WOULD YOU ALL EXCUSE ME
FOR A MOMENT?

30:57.811 --> 31:00.780
I GOT ONE JUST LIKE IT
IN BLUE,

31:00.780 --> 31:03.917
WITH SEQUINS RUNNING
ALL DOWN THE FRONT.

31:03.917 --> 31:07.787
OF COURSE, I'M GONNA NEED
NEW SHOES TO MATCH.

31:07.787 --> 31:11.224
YOU WOULDN'T MIND IF I TOOK
YOUR CREDIT CARD, WOULD YOU?

31:11.224 --> 31:12.792
OH, HEY.

31:12.792 --> 31:16.263
JUST SHOWING YOUR FATHER
MY NEW DRESS.

31:16.263 --> 31:18.164
I THINK
HE LIKES IT.

31:18.164 --> 31:20.767
MY DAUGHTER
CAME TO SEE ME TODAY.

31:20.767 --> 31:22.602
DAUGHTER?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

31:25.539 --> 31:30.243
SHE TOLD ME WHAT YOU DID,
DADDY.

31:30.243 --> 31:31.378
'CINDA,
PUT THAT THING DOWN.

31:31.378 --> 31:32.646
YOU'RE SCARING ME.

31:32.646 --> 31:36.249
I SPENT MY WHOLE LIFE
MAKING EXCUSES FOR YOU,

31:36.249 --> 31:38.385
BUT NO MORE,
OLD MAN.

31:38.385 --> 31:41.788
NO MORE!

31:41.788 --> 31:43.390
WHAT'S THAT?
HMM?

31:43.390 --> 31:46.760
YOU'RE TRYING TO TELL ME
YOU <i>DIDN'T</i> SEND HER AWAY?

31:46.760 --> 31:48.361
SPEAK UP, DADDY!

31:48.361 --> 31:49.629
I CAN'T HEAR YOU!

31:49.629 --> 31:51.498
AAH! MISS LUCINDA!

31:51.498 --> 31:53.133
NO,
I'M NOT DONE HERE!

31:53.133 --> 31:55.735
IF YOU GO TO JAIL,
YOU CAN'T BE WITH YOUR DAUGHTER.

32:02.709 --> 32:05.512
GIVE YOUR MAID A RAISE,
OLD MAN.

32:05.512 --> 32:07.681
SHE JUST
SAVED YOUR LIFE.

32:18.892 --> 32:20.827
A LITTLE GLAMOUR
FOR YOUR SHOWCASE.

32:20.827 --> 32:22.362
THANK YOU SO MUCH!

32:22.362 --> 32:23.763
[ CHUCKLES ]
OH!

32:23.763 --> 32:26.199
SO, YOU KNOW THE GIRLS AND I
WOULD LOVE TO COME TONIGHT.

32:26.199 --> 32:27.767
WHY?

32:27.767 --> 32:29.769
SO YOU CAN GIVE ME A STANDING
OVATION AND EMBARRASS ME?

32:29.769 --> 32:31.771
I PROMISE
WE WON'T STAND.

32:31.771 --> 32:33.506
THEN WHO NEEDS YOU?

32:33.506 --> 32:34.674
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:34.674 --> 32:36.343
SO, DID YOU TALK TO NICK
ABOUT OPAL

32:36.343 --> 32:37.811
AND HER DRAWER
OF MANY SECRETS?

32:37.811 --> 32:39.379
I'M WAITING
TILL HE GETS HOME.

32:39.379 --> 32:40.880
THE DEAD WIFE
DOING HER LESBIAN MAID

32:40.880 --> 32:42.816
SEEMS LIKE A TALK
WE SHOULD HAVE IN PERSON.

32:42.816 --> 32:45.785
BUT YOU <i>ARE</i> GONNA CONFRONT HIM
ABOUT NOT TELLING YOU.

32:45.785 --> 32:47.320
OH, YEAH.

32:47.320 --> 32:48.521
FINALLY!

32:48.521 --> 32:50.390
THE ELEGANT BADASS
IS BACK.

32:50.390 --> 32:52.892
THAT'S WHAT WE CALL YOU
WHEN YOU'RE NOT AROUND.

32:52.892 --> 32:54.394
REALLY?

32:54.394 --> 32:55.795
WELL, WE HAVEN'T
CALLED YOU THAT LATELY,

32:55.795 --> 32:58.498
NOT THE WAY YOU'VE BEEN
TIPTOEING AROUND NICHOLAS.

32:58.498 --> 33:01.901
I KNOW.
I HAVEN'T BEEN MYSELF.

33:01.901 --> 33:03.837
HOW COME?

33:03.837 --> 33:07.307
I WANT SO MUCH
FOR THIS TO WORK.

33:07.307 --> 33:10.543
WHEN THINGS
STARTED TO SEEM...OFF,

33:10.543 --> 33:14.514
I GUESS I JUST CLOSED MY EYES
A LITTLE.

33:14.514 --> 33:16.783
BUT NO MORE.

33:16.783 --> 33:19.285
GOOD FOR YOU.

33:19.285 --> 33:20.353
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:20.353 --> 33:21.554
WHAT ABOUT OPAL?

33:21.554 --> 33:22.856
ARE YOU GONNA CONFRONT HER,
TOO?

33:22.856 --> 33:24.224
NO.

33:24.224 --> 33:26.359
I'M NOT EVEN GONNA LET ON
THAT I KNOW.

33:26.359 --> 33:29.162
FROM NOW ON, I PLAY THIS GAME
THE WAY SHE DOES --

33:29.162 --> 33:32.132
WITH MY EYES OPEN,
MY MOUTH SHUT,

33:32.132 --> 33:34.668
AND MY CLAWS
BEHIND MY BACK.

33:34.668 --> 33:38.238
THAT'S MY ELEGANT BADASS.

33:38.238 --> 33:39.773
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:39.773 --> 33:42.642
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

33:48.181 --> 33:50.784
SO,
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

33:50.784 --> 33:56.790
I'M IMPRESSED WITH THE FOOD
AND THE WINE AND THIS HOUSE...

33:56.790 --> 33:58.692
AND THE COMPANY.

33:58.692 --> 34:01.728
IT'S ALL BEEN...
PERFECT.

34:01.728 --> 34:05.231
I COULD TAKE YOU
ON A TOUR LATER.

34:05.231 --> 34:07.367
MM.
I'D LIKE THAT.

34:07.367 --> 34:08.768
I JUST
HAD MY BEDROOM REDONE.

34:08.768 --> 34:09.903
I'VE BEEN DYING
TO SHOW IT OFF.

34:09.903 --> 34:13.506
YOUR BEDROOM?

34:13.506 --> 34:16.810
MM, I THINK
YOU'LL REALLY LIKE IT.

34:16.810 --> 34:18.745
WHAT'S WRONG?

34:21.214 --> 34:23.416
I HAVE A RECIPE
FOR ENCHILADAS.

34:23.416 --> 34:26.720
MY HUSBAND LOVED THEM.

34:26.720 --> 34:27.921
OKAY.

34:27.921 --> 34:30.490
I MAKE THEM WITH PORK
AND ZUCCHINI,

34:30.490 --> 34:32.892
WHICH ISN'T EVERYONE'S TASTE,
BUT...

34:32.892 --> 34:36.229
I'VE MADE THEM THE SAME WAY
FOR OVER 20 YEARS.

34:36.229 --> 34:38.264
WHY ARE YOU
TELLING ME THIS?

34:38.264 --> 34:41.234
I'M AFRAID
TO HAVE YOU TRY MY ENCHILADAS

34:41.234 --> 34:43.737
BECAUSE I'M NOT SURE
YOU'D LIKE THEM.

34:46.473 --> 34:47.607
OH.

34:47.607 --> 34:48.908
SEE,
AT THIS POINT IN MY LIFE,

34:48.908 --> 34:50.777
I DON'T THINK
I CAN MAKE THEM ANY OTHER WAY.

34:50.777 --> 34:52.212
[ SIGHS ]

34:52.212 --> 34:55.782
I'M SURE I'D ENJOY YOUR...
ENCHILADAS

34:55.782 --> 34:58.151
ANY WAY YOU SERVE THEM.

34:58.151 --> 34:59.786
I HOPE SO.

34:59.786 --> 35:02.555
I REALLY LIKE YOU.

35:02.555 --> 35:04.357
AND I LIKE YOU.

35:04.357 --> 35:06.426
YOU MAKE ME LAUGH.

35:06.426 --> 35:10.497
AND YOU MAKE ME FEEL GOOD
ABOUT MYSELF.

35:10.497 --> 35:14.434
I'VE BEEN NEEDING SOMEONE
TO DO THAT.

35:16.636 --> 35:18.438
I'M HAPPY TO OBLIGE.

35:18.438 --> 35:21.474
AND I'M IN NO RUSH
TO TRY YOUR...

35:21.474 --> 35:24.511
CAN WE PLEASE
DROP THIS METAPHOR?

35:24.511 --> 35:26.546
SURE.
I'M SORRY.

35:26.546 --> 35:27.680
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:27.680 --> 35:30.416
FOR NOW
WE CAN JUST BE FRIENDS.

35:30.416 --> 35:31.918
I WILL COOK FOR YOU

35:31.918 --> 35:34.687
AND YOU WILL TELL ME
CRAZY STORIES ABOUT YOUR BOSS

35:34.687 --> 35:39.225
AND WE WILL CONTINUE
TO HAVE A GREAT TIME.

35:39.225 --> 35:41.361
AND THEN, ONE NIGHT...

35:41.361 --> 35:43.630
THERE WILL BE MORE.

35:43.630 --> 35:47.600
AND IT WILL BE MAGICAL.

35:57.881 --> 35:58.782
[ APPLAUSE ]

36:01.952 --> 36:03.420
ALL RIGHT.

36:03.420 --> 36:04.821
AND UP NEXT,
WE HAVE AN AMAZING GAL.

36:04.821 --> 36:06.189
LET'S PUT OUR HANDS TOGETHER

36:06.189 --> 36:07.958
AND WELCOME TO THE STAGE
MISS CARMEN LUNA.

36:07.958 --> 36:10.694
[ APPLAUSE ]

36:16.533 --> 36:19.236
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

36:22.939 --> 36:28.411
♪ IN MY ROOM LATE AT NIGHT ♪

36:28.411 --> 36:35.485
♪ I THINK OF YOU
AND YOUR SAD EYES ♪

36:35.485 --> 36:44.261
♪ AND I ASK THE STARS
TO BRING YOU HOME ♪

36:44.261 --> 36:47.230
♪ OH, WE'LL DANCE IN THE RAIN ♪

36:47.230 --> 36:50.567
♪ COME HOME ♪

36:50.567 --> 36:54.938
♪ WE'LL POUR SOME CHAMPAGNE,
MY LOVE ♪

36:54.938 --> 36:57.374
♪ COME HOME ♪

36:57.374 --> 37:05.682
♪ WALK THROUGH THAT DOOR AND
THEN PROMISE ME YOU'LL STAY ♪

37:05.682 --> 37:08.785
SHE'S PRETTY GOOD,
HUH?

37:08.785 --> 37:12.255
SHE'S PERFECT.

37:21.698 --> 37:23.767
I THINK
WE SHOULD CALL THE POLICE.

37:23.767 --> 37:25.735
MISS LUCINDA
DIDN'T HURT ANYONE.

37:25.735 --> 37:28.838
BUT SHE SCARED KENNY TO DEATH,
AND HE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

37:28.838 --> 37:30.807
HE KEPT HER
FROM HER DAUGHTER.

37:30.807 --> 37:32.809
<i>THAT</i> IS SOMETHING.

37:32.809 --> 37:34.544
WELL,
I WANT HER OUT.

37:34.544 --> 37:37.280
I WON'T FEEL SAFE AS LONG
AS THAT LUNATIC IN STRETCH PANTS

37:37.280 --> 37:38.682
IS LIVING
IN THIS HOUSE.

37:38.682 --> 37:41.418
MR. REGGIE'S TALKING
TO MR. KENNETH RIGHT NOW.

37:41.418 --> 37:43.954
I'M SURE HE'LL FIND A WAY
TO MAKE THIS BETTER.

37:43.954 --> 37:46.556
Reggie: NOW, THE TRUTH IS,
I'M WORRIED.

37:46.556 --> 37:47.958
I WAS SUPPORTIVE

37:47.958 --> 37:49.826
WHEN YOU FIRST GAVE YOUR
POWER OF ATTORNEY TO LUCINDA

37:49.826 --> 37:52.495
BECAUSE I THOUGHT SHE HAD
YOUR BEST INTERESTS AT HEART.

37:56.399 --> 37:57.701
SHE'S CERTAINLY ANGRY.

37:57.701 --> 37:59.736
AND WITH
THAT POWER OF ATTORNEY,

37:59.736 --> 38:01.304
SHE COULD START
TO SELL YOUR STOCKS,

38:01.304 --> 38:03.306
TAKE MONEY
FROM YOUR ACCOUNT.

38:05.542 --> 38:07.811
SHE HAS
HER DAUGHTER BACK.

38:07.811 --> 38:10.180
SHE MIGHT WANT
TO PROVIDE FOR HER.

38:10.180 --> 38:11.781
AND PUNISH YOU.

38:13.750 --> 38:19.389
UNFORTUNATELY...THERE'S ONLY
SO MUCH I CAN DO TO STOP HER.

38:26.596 --> 38:29.165
YOU WANT <i>ME</i>
TO HAVE YOUR POWER OF ATTORNEY?

38:31.368 --> 38:33.737
THIS COULD RUFFLE
SOME FEATHERS.

38:39.676 --> 38:44.881
I...NEED YOU.

38:59.429 --> 39:01.398
WELCOME BACK.

39:01.398 --> 39:02.799
THANK YOU.

39:02.799 --> 39:05.535
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

39:05.535 --> 39:06.936
BETTER.

39:06.936 --> 39:10.673
THE DOCTORS SAID
NOW I JUST NEED LOTS OF REST.

39:10.673 --> 39:12.409
OF COURSE.

39:12.409 --> 39:16.546
I WANT TO APOLOGIZE FOR PRESSING
YOU ABOUT DAHLIA'S AFFAIR.

39:16.546 --> 39:18.415
I WAS
OUT OF LINE.

39:18.415 --> 39:20.283
YOU WERE.

39:20.283 --> 39:23.887
WELL,
PLEASE KNOW...

39:23.887 --> 39:27.323
I WON'T BE ASKING
ANY MORE QUESTIONS ABOUT IT.

39:27.323 --> 39:29.359
THANK YOU.

39:48.878 --> 39:50.947
[ GASPS ]
